A few words about translations:
-------------------------------

If you plan to translate omail-admin for your language (great idea!),
please get the newest strings.php file from the actual CVS :
http://cvs.sourceforge.net/cgi-bin/cvsweb.cgi/admin2/?cvsroot=oMail
and click on the "1.xx" in the front of "strings.php".


Then, there are entries looking like that:

$txt_firstname=array(   "ru"=>"éÍÑ",
                        "fr"=>"Prénom",
                        "de"=>"Vorname",
                        "da"=>"Fornavn",
                        "en"=>"Firstname",
                        "es"=>"Nombre",
                        "it"=>"Nome");

I would use a search-replace function, and replace 
"it"
by
"xx"=>"",\n                        "it"


Result:

$txt_firstname=array(   "ru"=>"éÍÑ",
                        "fr"=>"Prénom",
                        "de"=>"Vorname",
                        "da"=>"Fornavn",
                        "en"=>"Firstname",
                        "es"=>"Nombre",
                        "xx"=>"",
                        "it"=>"Nome");


And then, add your text. Please use the official 2-letters language name.

After testing the file, please send it me directely by email (omail@omnis.ch),
and I will merge it to the CVS.


-- om, 13oct2k
